sing American and British development of atomic weapons, subjected to FBI surveillance, and named as a fellow traveler on George Orwell's infamous list. His service as a British Royal Navy officer in the First World War prepared Blackett to take a scientific advisory role on military matters in the mid-1930s. An international leader in the experimental techniques of the cloud chamber, he was a pioneer in the application of magnetic evidence for the geophysical theory of continental drift. But his strong political stands made him a polarizing influence, and the decisions he made capture the complexity of living a prominent twentieth-century scientific life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aKernfysica. 0aNuclear physicists. 0aPhysik. 0aTweede Wereldoorlog. 4aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Science & Technology. 4aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain. 4aHISTORY / General. 4aNuclear physicists -- Great Britain -- Biography. 4aWorld War, 1939-1945 -- Science. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Military.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: World History eBook Packagez9783110353563oZDB-23-HWH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013 (Canada)z978311075606708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831104422050 cprintz978067433573840uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067433575240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674335752423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674335752/original  a978-3-11-044220-5  Harvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-075606-7  HUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013 (Can